%25%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F3Cv32%2F33%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Consumer%20price%20index%20inflation%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22454%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ECore%20CPI%2C%20which%20excludes%20volatile%20food%20and%20energy%20prices%2C%20increased%203.2%25%20over%20the%20year%20in%20December%2C%20below%20the%20expected%20forecast%20of%203.3%25%2C%20which%20would%20have%20matched%20November's%20rate.%20The%20rate%20had%20been%203.3%25%20for%20three%20consecutive%20months%20before%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year-over-year%20percent%20change%20in%20the%20shelter%20index%20continued%20to%20slow.%20The%20shelter%20index%20increased%204.6%25%20over%20the%20year%20in%20December%2C%20down%20from%20the%206%25%20year-over-year%20increase%20in%20January%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CPI%20climbed%200.4%25%20over%20the%20month%20in%20December%2C%20matching%20the%20forecast%20and%20above%20November's%200.3%25%20increase.%20BLS%20said%20in%20a%20news%20release%20that%20energy%20contributed%20more%20than%2040%25%20of%20that%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gasoline%20index%20rose%204.4%25%20over%20the%20month%2C%20higher%20than%20the%20previous%200.6%25%20increase.%20The%20fuel%20oil%20index%20saw%20a%20similar%20story%20%E2%80%94%20it%20increased%204.4%25%20in%20December%20after%20rising%200.6%25%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECore%20CPI%20rose%200.2%25%20from%20November%20to%20December.%20It%20was%20expected%20to%20continue%20rising%20by%200.3%25%2C%20as%20it%20had%20done%20for%20four%20straight%20months%20before%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20takeaway%20for%20consumers%20is%20that%20the%20pressure%20on%20household%20budgets%20is%20unrelenting%2C%26quot%3B%20Greg%20McBride%2C%20chief%20financial%20analyst%20for%20Bankrate%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20could%20consider%20the%20new%20data%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-federal-reserve-final-decision-powell-trump-inflation-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest%20rate%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month.%20After%20three%20consecutive%20cuts%2C%20there%20likely%20won't%20be%20another%20interest%20rate%20cut%20just%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraders%20have%20been%20expecting%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20to%20hold%20the%20Fed's%20target%20rate%20steady%20at%202025's%20first%20scheduled%20meeting.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECME%20FedWatch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20indicates%20what%20traders%20expect%20to%20happen%20to%20rates%20based%20on%20market%20activity%2C%20showed%20before%20the%20CPI%20release%20a%2097%25%20chance%20the%20Fed's%20target%20rate%20would%20be%20unchanged.%20That%20probability%20was%20little%20changed%20after%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20consumer%20reaction%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20different%20than%20the%20market%20reaction%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20the%20market%20is%20going%20to%20look%20at%20the%20improvement%20in%20the%20core%20and%20take%20that%20as%20good%20news%20and%20rejoice%2C%26quot%3B%20McBride%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20consumers'%20household%20budgets%20are%20based%20on%20the%20headline%2C%20and%20the%20food%20and%20energy%20costs%20are%20both%20rising%20at%20a%20faster%20than%20desired%20pace%20and%20pressuring%20already%20tight%20household%20budgets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFed%20chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20said%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20December%2018%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Committee%20will%20assess%20incoming%20data%2C%20the%20evolving%20outlook%2C%20and%20the%20balance%20of%20risks%26quot%3B%20when%20figuring%20out%20any%20additional%20changes%20to%20its%20target%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20reducing%20policy%20restraint%20too%20fast%20or%20too%20much%20could%20hinder%20progress%20on%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said%20after%20the%20most%20recent%20interest-rate%20decision.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20reducing%20policy%20restraint%20too%20slowly%20or%20too%20little%20could%20unduly%20weaken%20economic%20activity%20and%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdecember-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-employment-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20published%20last%20Friday%2C%20showed%20job%20growth%20exceeded%20the%20forecast%20in%20December%2C%20while%20unemployment%20fell%20from%204.2%25%20in%20November%20to%204.1%25%20in%20December.%20Cory%20Stahle%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20said%20the%20labor%20market%20report%20%26quot%3Bvalidates%20the%20stance%20that%20we've%20seen%20from%20the%20Fed%20recently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-december-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736947938000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6786d37d50dfd88e193e68de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-december-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20inflation%20continued%20to%20heat%20up%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024.%20The%20consumer%20price%20index%20rose%202.9%25%20year-over-year%20in%20December%2C%20above%20November's%202.7%25%20rate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2